<item>
            <title>[AMQ-3374] Long KahaDB transactions could lead to OutOfMemory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3374</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Problem: all writes are kept in memory until the sync time, which for long transactions could be a problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solution: define max transaction size and if threshold is reached keep the rest of the writes in a temp file&lt;/p&gt;</description>
